  "directions": [
    {
      "text": "Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper liners.",
      "duration": "5. min",
      "id": 1509391087542
    },
    {
      "text": "Whisk chocolate chips, brown sugar, flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and salt together in a bowl. Whisk soy milk, oil, applesauce, eggs, vinegar, and vanilla extract together in a separate bowl; stir into flour mixture until batter is just combined. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups until each cup is 3/4-full.",
      "duration": "15 min.",
      "id": 1509391413599
    },
    {
      "text": "Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.",
